\section{Recommended starting points}{


New users should start with \code{vignette("getting-started", package = "shewhartr")} for a 5-minute overview, then move to the chart family
that matches their data type. The vignette \code{"phase1-phase2"}
explains the central distinction between estimation and monitoring,
and \code{"arl-simulation"} shows how to evaluate the operating
characteristics of any chart configuration.
}

